    fix(cli): 0.88 parity — workspace-folder defaults to cwd, error-path alignment
    
    0.88 made --workspace-folder optional across up/build/exec/read-configuration/
    run-user-commands, defaulting to process.cwd() when no workspace/id-label/
    container-id/override-config is given. Mirror that, and align the error paths
    the change exposed:
    
    - up: id-label with no container and no workspace now reports "No dev container
      config and no workspace found." (matches 0.88).
    - read-configuration: exits 1 silently (banner only, no error envelope) when no
      config is found, via a typed config.ConfigNotFoundError + ExitCodeError.
    - parity matrix extractErrorReason: ignore the TS version banner and Node stack
      frames, strip the log-timestamp prefix and a leading "Error: " so a TS-thrown
      error lines up with Go's plain message.
    
    Contract lane green.
    
